.TH "gnutls_psk_allocate_server_credentials2" 3 "3.8.13" "gnutls" "gnutls"
.SH NAME
gnutls_psk_allocate_server_credentials2 \- API function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <gnutls/gnutls.h>
.sp
.BI "int gnutls_psk_allocate_server_credentials2(gnutls_psk_server_credentials_t * " sc ", gnutls_mac_algorithm_t " mac ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gnutls_psk_server_credentials_t * sc" 12
is a pointer to a \fBgnutls_psk_server_credentials_t\fP type.
.IP "gnutls_mac_algorithm_t mac" 12
encryption algorithm to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a gnutls_psk_server_credentials_t structure and initializes
the HMAC binder algorithm to  \fImac\fP . If  \fImac\fP is set to GNUTLS_MAC_UNKNOWN
both possible algorithms SHA384 and SHA256 are applied to find a matching
binder value.
.SH "RETURNS"
On success, \fBGNUTLS_E_SUCCESS\fP (0) is returned, otherwise
an error code is returned.
